00:50:40,346 --> 00:50:45,810
Thumb to palm, index finger
through little digit, smartly aligned,

725
00:50:45,851 --> 00:50:48,437
sharp to the hairline,
down !

726
00:50:53,150 --> 00:50:55,486
Too many men,
far better than you,

727
00:50:55,528 --> 00:50:58,239
have executed
that courtesy.

728
00:50:58,322 --> 00:51:01,867
And if you're smart,
you won't try it again.

729
00:51:05,329 --> 00:51:10,376
This bat has got sharper radar
than the Nautilus.

730
00:51:10,459 --> 00:51:12,920
Don't fuck with me,
Charlie.

731
00:51:23,431 --> 00:51:25,933
See you get
a good night's sleep, son.

732
00:51:35,276 --> 00:51:38,321
[ Groaning ]

733
00:51:38,404 --> 00:51:41,032
[ Frank ]
?It's a lovely day today ?

734
00:51:41,115 --> 00:51:44,076
?So, whatever
you gotta do ?

735
00:51:44,160 --> 00:51:47,079
?You got a lovely day
to do it in that's true ?

736
00:51:53,377 --> 00:51:55,379
Good morning, Charlie.

737
00:51:58,215 --> 00:52:01,844
- [ Sigh ] Good morning.
- This is Sofia, Charlie.

738
00:52:01,928 --> 00:52:04,430
She's a magician
with a needle.

739
00:52:04,513 --> 00:52:07,475
Sofia's workin' me up
a little "Glen Plaid" number,

740
00:52:07,558 --> 00:52:10,228
and I've asked her if she'd
put something together for you.

741
00:52:10,311 --> 00:52:13,898
- Uh, I don't need any clothes, Colonel.
- Standard issue...

742
00:52:13,981 --> 00:52:16,567
for an upscale
urban assignment.

743
00:52:16,651 --> 00:52:19,320
You don't like the clothes,
Charlie, on completion of duty,

744
00:52:19,362 --> 00:52:21,572
you can give 'em away.

745
00:52:21,656 --> 00:52:24,992
Juice, coffee, and other assorted
goodies on the trolley over there.

746
00:52:25,034 --> 00:52:27,286
Get yourself up,
get yourself together !

747
00:52:27,370 --> 00:52:30,831
?It's a great day
for singin' a song ?

748
00:52:30,915 --> 00:52:34,835
?And it's a great day
for movin' along ?

749
00:52:34,877 --> 00:52:37,463
?And it's a great day
from morning to night ?

750
00:52:37,546 --> 00:52:41,008
?And it's
a great day ?

751
00:52:41,092 --> 00:52:44,262
for everybody's plight.

752
00:52:44,345 --> 00:52:47,056
[ Frank Chuckling ]

753
00:52:48,724 --> 00:52:50,893
How are you feeling
today, Colonel ?

754
00:52:50,977 --> 00:52:54,230
Super !
Superior !

755
00:52:54,313 --> 00:52:57,108
Superfluous !

756
00:52:57,191 --> 00:52:59,318
Young Sofie here
is working Thanksgiving...

757
00:52:59,402 --> 00:53:01,612
because she's trying to
put herself through college.

758
00:53:01,696 --> 00:53:05,199
I told her, "My young friend
Charlie's headed for college."

759
00:53:05,241 --> 00:53:07,868
- Uh, excuse me.
- Where you goin' ?

760
00:53:07,952 --> 00:53:11,581
- I-l need to use the phone.
- What's wrong with the phones in here ?

761
00:53:11,664 --> 00:53:14,208
I don't want
to disturb you.

762
00:53:14,292 --> 00:53:16,335
You're not disturbing me.
Make your call.

763
00:53:16,419 --> 00:53:18,588
I'd kinda like
to be private.

764
00:53:18,671 --> 00:53:21,632
Stay outta my room !

765
00:53:21,716 --> 00:53:24,427
This is as private
as you're gonna get.

766
00:53:27,096 --> 00:53:31,809
?But if you've got somethin'
that must be done ?

767
00:53:31,893 --> 00:53:35,980
?And it can only
be done by one ?

768
00:53:37,064 --> 00:53:39,817
Sofia...

769
00:53:39,901 --> 00:53:43,404
what are the chances
of suitin' you up sometime ?

770
00:53:43,487 --> 00:53:46,449
- [ Operator ] Sugarbush Lodge.
- George Willis, please.

771
00:53:49,452 --> 00:53:52,872
- [ George ] Hello !
- George ! Hey, it's Charlie.

772
00:53:52,955 --> 00:53:56,083
Hey, Chas. Next year you gotta
come up with us.

773
00:53:56,167 --> 00:54:01,255
White powder on
a base of snow bunnies.

774
00:54:01,297 --> 00:54:03,966
Chas,
are you there ?

775
00:54:04,050 --> 00:54:06,260
Yeah, I'm here.
Um --

776
00:54:06,302 --> 00:54:09,430
- you told me to call you for the moves.
- All right.

777
00:54:09,513 --> 00:54:12,308
For now, the move's
no move: status quo.

778
00:54:12,391 --> 00:54:14,310
Everything's
the way we left it.

779
00:54:14,393 --> 00:54:16,979
How did we leave it ?

780
00:54:17,063 --> 00:54:20,733
See no evil,
hear no evil.

781
00:54:20,816 --> 00:54:24,362
You know
what I mean, Chas ?

782
00:54:24,445 --> 00:54:27,323
Yeah. See no evil,
hear no evil.

783
00:54:29,575 --> 00:54:34,789
- Okay, then, walk like you talk !
- All right, good-bye.

784
00:54:34,872 --> 00:54:39,919
- George Willis, huh ?
- Yeah.

785
00:54:40,002 --> 00:54:41,921
George Willis.

786
00:54:42,004 --> 00:54:45,925
That makes his father probably
George Willis, Senior.

787
00:54:46,008 --> 00:54:47,927
Charlie, I ask ya,

788
00:54:48,010 --> 00:54:51,889
what do you think Big George
is gonna feel about Little George...

789
00:54:51,973 --> 00:54:55,017
seeing no evil,
hearing no evil ?

790
00:54:57,603 --> 00:54:59,730
Well, we're not gonna
tell our parents.

791
00:54:59,814 --> 00:55:02,692
We're just gonna keep it
between ourselves.

792
00:55:02,775 --> 00:55:06,946
Oh, George isn't gonna tell
his father about this thing !

793
00:55:07,029 --> 00:55:09,865
Damn decent of him.
Ooh ! Aw ! Hah !

794
00:55:09,949 --> 00:55:12,243
- Scusi.
- Prego.

795
00:55:12,326 --> 00:55:14,704
I love it
when you hurt me.

796
00:55:14,787 --> 00:55:17,248
Uh, tell me now,
Charlie.

797
00:55:17,331 --> 00:55:21,294
This, uh, George Willis, Junior,
what's his father do ?

798
00:55:21,377 --> 00:55:23,421
I don't really know.

799
00:55:23,504 --> 00:55:26,048
Well, I'm gonna tell ya.

800
00:55:26,132 --> 00:55:30,886
When George Willis, Sr., isn't busy as a
million-dollar man for Aetna Casualty --

801
00:55:30,970 --> 00:55:34,390
or is it New England Distributor
for the Chrysler Corporation ?

802
00:55:34,473 --> 00:55:38,477
He concerns himself with his young son,
George Willis, Junior.

803
00:55:38,561 --> 00:55:41,898
George isn't going
to say anything to his father.

804
00:55:41,939 --> 00:55:44,233
Oh, Charlie.

805
00:55:44,275 --> 00:55:46,485
Big George is gonna
wind up Little George,

806
00:55:46,569 --> 00:55:49,697
and Little George is gonna sing
like a canary.

807
00:55:49,739 --> 00:55:52,283
And if you're hip, kid,
you're gonna hop to, too.

808
00:55:52,366 --> 00:55:54,452
You've got this
all figured out, don't you ?

809
00:55:54,535 --> 00:55:58,915
It don't take no Young America merit
scholarship to figure this one out.

810
00:55:58,998 --> 00:56:02,877
Charlie, you had a little life,
so you decided to go to Baird...

811
00:56:02,919 --> 00:56:06,005
to put yourself in the market
for a big one.

812
00:56:06,088 --> 00:56:08,049
Now, in order to stay
in the running,

813
00:56:08,090 --> 00:56:10,968
you're gonna have to tell these people
what they want to know.

814
00:56:11,052 --> 00:56:13,220
You think so ?

815
00:56:13,304 --> 00:56:15,264
- Are we finished, Sofia ?
- Yes.

816
00:56:15,306 --> 00:56:18,184
Grazie. Grazie.

817
00:56:19,977 --> 00:56:22,563
Charlie,

818
00:56:22,605 --> 00:56:25,483
if you don't sing now,

819
00:56:25,566 --> 00:56:28,861
you're gonna end up,
not only shelving biscuits...

820
00:56:28,945 --> 00:56:31,906
in some convenience store
in the Oregon burbs,

821
00:56:31,989 --> 00:56:36,202
probably the last word you'll ever hear
yourself say just before you croak...

822
00:56:36,285 --> 00:56:40,248
gonna be, "Have a nice day
and come back soon."

823
00:56:40,331 --> 00:56:42,500
Sofia !

824
00:56:42,583 --> 00:56:46,545
Measure up Charlie, pronto.
We got a date for Thanksgiving.

825
00:56:46,629 --> 00:56:48,631
We got a date ?

826
00:56:48,714 --> 00:56:50,883
My brother's place.

827
00:56:50,967 --> 00:56:53,719
W.R. Slade,
White Plains, New York.

828
00:56:53,803 --> 00:56:57,265
Colonel, I can't go with you
to your brother's place.

829
00:56:57,306 --> 00:57:00,101
I mean, I should be
getting back to school.

830
00:57:02,478 --> 00:57:06,941
Uh, well you gotta have
Thanksgiving somewhere.

831
00:57:07,024 --> 00:57:10,820
I mean, eats and treats.
I could use the company.

832
00:57:14,448 --> 00:57:17,368
All right.
D-Does he know I'm comin' ?

833
00:57:17,451 --> 00:57:20,371
He doesn't know I'm comin'. But wait
till you see the look on his face...

834
00:57:20,454 --> 00:57:22,373
when I walk through
the door.

835
00:57:22,456 --> 00:57:25,126
Oh, he loves me !

836
00:57:26,460 --> 00:57:30,339
Oh, uh, Charlie,
about your little problem,

837
00:57:30,423 --> 00:57:32,925
there are two kinds of people
in this world:

838
00:57:33,009 --> 00:57:35,428
those who stand up
and face the music,

839
00:57:35,511 --> 00:57:37,430
and those who
run for cover.

840
00:57:37,513 --> 00:57:41,100
Cover's better.
Okay, Sofia, suit 'im up !

841
00:57:41,183 --> 00:57:44,812
Make him pretty !

842
00:57:59,160 --> 00:58:02,121
Careful.

843
00:58:02,163 --> 00:58:05,082
- Should I ring it ?
- Yeah.

844
00:58:11,631 --> 00:58:13,633
Yes ?

845
00:58:13,716 --> 00:58:16,177
Yes !
Who is this ?

846
00:58:16,260 --> 00:58:20,640
- It's Randy.
- Randy ? You new ?

847
00:58:20,681 --> 00:58:22,850
I'm your nephew.

848
00:58:22,934 --> 00:58:25,603
Hah !
Here I am !

849
00:58:25,686 --> 00:58:28,856
Your sister's been
hoarding me long enough.

850
00:58:28,940 --> 00:58:31,859
- Thought it's time to spread
the riches around.
- Uncle Frank !

851
00:58:31,943 --> 00:58:33,903
- Gloria !
- Gail.

852
00:58:33,986 --> 00:58:35,905
Of course.

853
00:58:35,988 --> 00:58:39,450
Say hello to the potluck
party from New York City.

854
00:58:39,533 --> 00:58:42,578
Good old Uncle Frank and this here
with him is Charlie Simms,

855
00:58:42,662 --> 00:58:44,956
star halfback of the
Baird football team.

856
00:58:44,997 --> 00:58:49,252
They not only beat Exeter and Groton,
but Aquinas High School too.

857
00:58:49,335 --> 00:58:51,837
Where's your
miserable father ?

858
00:58:51,921 --> 00:58:54,465
Wait ! No, no.
Let's surprise him.

859
00:58:54,507 --> 00:58:57,593
Give that fat heart
of his an attack. Willie !

860
00:58:59,887 --> 00:59:02,765
Oh, Willie !

861
00:59:13,109 --> 00:59:15,111
Hello, Frank.

862
00:59:15,194 --> 00:59:18,573
- How you doin' ?
- Okay.

863
00:59:18,656 --> 00:59:23,452
Here's my hand.
Charlie, meet W.R. Slade.

864
00:59:23,536 --> 00:59:25,580
Nice to meet you, sir.

865
00:59:25,663 --> 00:59:28,541
The original bulging
briefcase man.

866
00:59:28,624 --> 00:59:33,045
Gretchen, I smell those prunes !
We talkin' Turkey Marbella ?

867
00:59:33,087 --> 00:59:35,840
- Yes, we are.
- Whoo !

868
00:59:35,923 --> 00:59:38,593
Let's have a whiff.
Come on.

869
00:59:38,676 --> 00:59:40,636
You know, I always had a sneaker
for you. Come here.

870
00:59:40,720 --> 00:59:42,847
[ Sniffing ]
Mmm.

871
00:59:42,930 --> 00:59:44,890
Hah !

872
00:59:44,932 --> 00:59:49,186
- Where are you, Garry ?
I heard you cough.
- Who are you again ?

873
00:59:49,228 --> 00:59:53,858
I'm just here at the Waldorf-Astoria
with -- Is it your brother ?

874
00:59:53,941 --> 00:59:56,402
W.R.'s final issue.
How ya doin' ?

875
00:59:56,444 --> 01:00:01,532
- Yes. Who the hell are you ?
- I'm kinda takin' care
of him for the weekend.

876
01:00:01,616 --> 01:00:02,742
Charlie !

877
01:00:02,825 --> 01:00:05,036
Jesus !

878
01:00:05,077 --> 01:00:09,624
Sorry. Where's the booze ?
Flowin' like mud here.

879
01:00:09,707 --> 01:00:13,961
To tell the truth, the colonel's
not well, I don't think.

880
01:00:14,045 --> 01:00:17,131
- Not well ?
- I think he's a little lonely.

881
01:00:17,214 --> 01:00:20,092
Why didn't you take him
to your family's for dinner ?

882
01:00:20,176 --> 01:00:22,803
I heard that !

883
01:00:22,887 --> 01:00:25,264
I heard that.

884
01:00:25,348 --> 01:00:27,975
Pay no attention to him.
That's his big-brother talk.

885
01:00:28,059 --> 01:00:30,728
He's been watching out for me
since day one.

886
01:00:30,770 --> 01:00:35,316
Bailed me out of more trouble...
than he'd like to remember.

887
01:00:35,399 --> 01:00:37,902
- Hmm ?
- [ Gretchen ] Let me take your coat.

888
01:00:37,985 --> 01:00:42,448
I meant to pick up some vino
on my way, but I blew it.

889
01:00:42,531 --> 01:00:44,992
I'll send you the Rothschild
again for Christmas,

890
01:00:45,076 --> 01:00:48,996
- only let's see how Thanksgiving goes.
- I'll set two more places.

891
01:00:49,080 --> 01:00:52,416
- Here's your drink, Frank.
- Thank you, Randy.

892
01:00:52,458 --> 01:00:55,086
Still with
Snow Queen sugar ?

893
01:00:55,127 --> 01:00:58,965
Snow Flake. Why do you
always get that wrong ?

894
01:00:59,048 --> 01:01:02,343
Because it's not important for me to
get it right. What are you doing there ?

895
01:01:02,426 --> 01:01:05,680
I'm Vice President
for Marketing.

896
01:01:05,763 --> 01:01:09,725
Whoo-ah ! Congratulations !
Sugar is shit, though.

897
01:01:09,809 --> 01:01:13,229
I told General Abrams to install
honey in the commissaries.

898
01:01:13,312 --> 01:01:16,607
If the K-50s didn't blow your brains
out, sugar, sure as shit, was gonna.

899
01:01:18,192 --> 01:01:20,528
- Why don't we all sit down ?
- Ooh !

900
01:01:20,611 --> 01:01:24,532
Mitsouki. Rhymes with nookie.
Be careful.

901
01:01:24,615 --> 01:01:28,578
- When the wife gets restless,
the wife gets racy.
- Let's go and eat.

902
01:01:28,661 --> 01:01:33,583
By all means.
Thank you, Charlie.

903
01:01:33,666 --> 01:01:37,795
Where you wanna sit, Frank, or you gonna
arrange yourself at the head again ?

904
01:01:37,878 --> 01:01:42,133
Any old card table
will do. This is fine.

905
01:01:42,216 --> 01:01:45,469
[ Frank ]
Where was I ? Oh !

906
01:01:45,511 --> 01:01:48,931
I wake up. It's four in the morning.
I don't know who I'm with,

907
01:01:49,015 --> 01:01:51,225
why I'm there
and where I am.

908
01:01:51,309 --> 01:01:54,270
What am I gonna do ?
I got this Asian flower,

909
01:01:54,353 --> 01:01:58,816
all giggly and dewy-like;

910
01:01:58,900 --> 01:02:02,778
and this hard-boiled
navy nurse outta Omaha, on the other.

911
01:02:02,862 --> 01:02:07,158
We're three across the bed,
not a stitch of clothes on.

912
01:02:07,199 --> 01:02:09,619
It comes to me.

913
01:02:09,702 --> 01:02:14,290
Let east meet west.
We'll build a golden bridge.

914
01:02:14,373 --> 01:02:16,083
[ Frank ]
Hah-hah !

915
01:02:16,167 --> 01:02:18,836
I felt like I'd just joined
the corps of engineers !

916
01:02:23,716 --> 01:02:26,385
We all still here ?

917
01:02:26,469 --> 01:02:29,889
It's a beautiful story.
[ Cough ]

918
01:02:32,099 --> 01:02:36,687
- Do you always enjoy
shocking people, Uncle Frank ?
- Honey.

919
01:02:36,771 --> 01:02:39,065
I didn't know you were
so easily shocked.

920
01:02:39,148 --> 01:02:41,692
I admire your sensibilities.
I'm touched.

921
01:02:41,776 --> 01:02:44,820
Dad, remember the time
you persuaded Frank...

922
01:02:44,904 --> 01:02:48,241
- to go to the kennel ?
- What about it ?

923
01:02:48,324 --> 01:02:51,619
- He almost put the seeing eye
dog business outta business.
- Cool it, Randy.

924
01:02:51,702 --> 01:02:55,873
- It's over and done with.
- Indeed it is, Garry.

925
01:02:55,957 --> 01:02:58,292
Indeed it is.
So is dinner.

926
01:02:58,376 --> 01:03:01,462
Charlie, what time do you have ?
I think we better be gettin' back.

927
01:03:01,545 --> 01:03:06,467
- You ever given any thought
to a braille watch, Frank ?
- Randy.

928
01:03:06,550 --> 01:03:10,513
- Stevie Wonder wears one,
or do you rank on him too ?
- Honey, please.

929
01:03:10,596 --> 01:03:12,890
It's all right, Gloria.
I enjoy Randy's observations.

930
01:03:12,932 --> 01:03:16,894
My wife's name is Gail, Frank.
Can you hear that ? Gail.

931
01:03:16,978 --> 01:03:19,438
Excuse me.
Gail.

932
01:03:19,522 --> 01:03:23,276
Gail strikes me as
a very beautiful woman,

933
01:03:23,359 --> 01:03:25,945
but there's a
little tension in her voice.

934
01:03:26,028 --> 01:03:28,823
It could be one
of two things:

935
01:03:28,906 --> 01:03:31,284
either Gail is nervous
or unsatisfied.

936
01:03:31,993 --> 01:03:35,830
What's your point,
Uncle Frank ?

937
01:03:35,830 --> 01:03:38,165
You oughta go down
on her.

938
01:03:38,207 --> 01:03:40,334
Cut it out, Frank,
will ya ?

939
01:03:40,418 --> 01:03:43,796
You're so wrapped up in sugar, you've
forgotten the taste of real honey !

940
01:03:43,838 --> 01:03:45,715
Frank,
for God's sake !

941
01:03:45,798 --> 01:03:48,426
Hear that voice ?
There's fire under that dress.

942
01:03:48,509 --> 01:03:50,595
- Will you cut it out ?
- Just get the fuck outta here.

943
01:03:50,678 --> 01:03:53,097
- Whoo-ah !
- Get in your limousine.

944
01:03:53,180 --> 01:03:56,350
Go down to the bowery, get with the
other fucking drunks where you belong !

945
01:03:56,434 --> 01:03:58,603
- Wait a minute.
- What ?

946
01:03:58,686 --> 01:04:01,647
- Could you take it easy ?
- What for ?

947
01:04:01,689 --> 01:04:04,191
You want me to lay off him,
Chuckie, 'cause he's blind ?

948
01:04:04,275 --> 01:04:07,236
- No, but I mean --
- My friend's name is Charles.

949
01:04:07,320 --> 01:04:09,822
He doesn't like
to be called Chuckie.

950
01:04:09,864 --> 01:04:13,534
- This is supposed to be a family
get-together. This is --
- A warning.

951
01:04:13,618 --> 01:04:17,788
Jesus Christ. Another sucker who thinks
this shitheel's a war hero.

952
01:04:17,872 --> 01:04:20,750
Whoo-ah.

953
01:04:22,209 --> 01:04:25,379
Well, once... maybe.

