1195
01:22:21,539 --> 01:22:26,252
- Donna ? I'm Frank. This here is --
- This is Charlie.

1196
01:22:26,335 --> 01:22:28,462
Yes. She likes you.

1197
01:22:28,546 --> 01:22:31,757
Charlie's having a difficult weekend.
He's going through a crisis.

1198
01:22:31,841 --> 01:22:34,594
How does he look
like he's holding up ?

1199
01:22:34,677 --> 01:22:37,638
He looks fine to me.

1200
01:22:37,680 --> 01:22:40,141
Oh ! She does
like you, Charlie.

1201
01:22:44,812 --> 01:22:47,064
So, Donna,

1202
01:22:47,148 --> 01:22:48,858
ah...

1203
01:22:48,941 --> 01:22:50,943
do you tango ?

1204
01:22:51,027 --> 01:22:54,614
No. I wanted
to learn once, but --

1205
01:22:54,697 --> 01:22:57,074
But ?

1206
01:22:57,158 --> 01:22:59,744
But Michael
didn't want to.

1207
01:22:59,827 --> 01:23:03,205
Michael, the one
you're waiting for.

1208
01:23:03,289 --> 01:23:07,001
Michael thinks
the tango's hysterical.

1209
01:23:07,084 --> 01:23:10,338
Well, I think
Michael's hysterical.

1210
01:23:10,421 --> 01:23:13,633
Don't pay any attention to him.
Did I already say that ?

1211
01:23:15,551 --> 01:23:18,054
What a beautiful laugh.

1212
01:23:19,555 --> 01:23:21,557
Thank you, Frank.

1213
01:23:26,312 --> 01:23:29,440
Would you like to learn
to tango, Donna ?

1214
01:23:32,526 --> 01:23:34,528
Right now ?

1215
01:23:34,570 --> 01:23:39,242
I'm offering you my services...
free of charge.

1216
01:23:39,325 --> 01:23:41,285
What do you say ?

1217
01:23:41,369 --> 01:23:43,162
Ah...

1218
01:23:43,246 --> 01:23:46,374
I think I'd be
a little afraid.

1219
01:23:46,457 --> 01:23:48,626
Of what ?

1220
01:23:48,709 --> 01:23:52,964
Afraid of making
a mistake.

1221
01:23:53,047 --> 01:23:57,343
No mistakes in the tango,
not like life.

1222
01:23:57,426 --> 01:24:00,012
It's simple. That's what makes
the tango so great.

1223
01:24:00,096 --> 01:24:04,934
If you make a mistake,
get all tangled up, just tango on.

1224
01:24:05,017 --> 01:24:08,521
[ Frank ]
Why don't you try ?

1225
01:24:12,316 --> 01:24:14,944
Will you try it ?

1226
01:24:15,027 --> 01:24:18,531
All right.
I'll give it a try.

1227
01:24:18,614 --> 01:24:21,284
Hold me down, son.

1228
01:24:28,332 --> 01:24:30,793
Your arm.

1229
01:24:32,587 --> 01:24:35,214
Charlie,

1230
01:24:35,298 --> 01:24:37,842
I'm gonna need some
coordinates here, son.

1231
01:24:37,925 --> 01:24:40,886
The floor's
about 20 by 30,

1232
01:24:40,970 --> 01:24:43,931
And you're at
the long end.

1233
01:24:44,015 --> 01:24:48,019
There's tables on the outside.
The band's on the right.

1234
01:27:26,844 --> 01:27:31,515
Oh, Frank, you are
one incredible dancer.

1235
01:27:34,060 --> 01:27:37,730
Wait'll you see
Charlie dance.

1236
01:27:37,813 --> 01:27:40,942
- He's a liar. I don't dance.
- Isn't he a charmer, though ?

1237
01:27:41,025 --> 01:27:45,196
Truth is, not only can he dance,
but he'll sing you a hell of a tune.

1238
01:27:45,279 --> 01:27:47,949
He can do bird calls
and imitate Bela Lugosi.

1239
01:27:48,032 --> 01:27:50,076
- Hi, honey.
- Hey.

1240
01:27:50,159 --> 01:27:53,788
Michael, this is Frank
and this is Charlie.

1241
01:27:53,871 --> 01:27:57,500
-Hi, Frank, Charlie. I'm sorry I'm late.
-Oh, that's okay.

1242
01:27:57,583 --> 01:28:00,294
These two gentlemen
entertained me,

1243
01:28:00,336 --> 01:28:02,964
and time flew.

1244
01:28:03,047 --> 01:28:06,842
Your girl is...
a hell of a tango dancer.

1245
01:28:06,926 --> 01:28:09,553
You found someone to tango with.
That's terrific !

1246
01:28:09,637 --> 01:28:11,639
Let me
shake your hand.

1247
01:28:11,722 --> 01:28:14,976
- No, it was Frank.
- Hell, I'll shake both your hands !

1248
01:28:16,477 --> 01:28:19,272
Honey, this looks like the place,
but we gotta go.

1249
01:28:19,355 --> 01:28:22,441
We got a date with Darryl
and Carol in the village.

1250
01:28:22,525 --> 01:28:24,443
Do you have a check ?

1251
01:28:24,527 --> 01:28:29,198
- Michael, please. My pleasure.
- No, no. I got this.

1252
01:28:29,282 --> 01:28:32,118
Michael, get your hand outta
your pocket. I'll take it. Really.

1253
01:28:32,201 --> 01:28:35,705
Allow me.

1254
01:28:35,788 --> 01:28:38,332
Why, thank you.

1255
01:28:38,374 --> 01:28:40,376
Bye, guys.

1256
01:28:40,418 --> 01:28:42,587
Bye.

1257
01:28:49,760 --> 01:28:53,598
Darryl and Carol.
Yeah.

1258
01:29:01,564 --> 01:29:04,859
[ Manny ] It's Apartment 17 E, Colonel.
She's expecting you.

1259
01:29:04,942 --> 01:29:08,863
You don't have to worry about a thing.
She's the creme de la creme.

1260
01:29:08,905 --> 01:29:11,407
My buddy took the Vice Chancellor
of Germany to her.

1261
01:29:11,490 --> 01:29:13,910
Now he wants to immigrate
to this country.

1262
01:29:13,993 --> 01:29:16,037
[ Frank ]
You did good, hombre.

1263
01:29:18,414 --> 01:29:21,250
My hair,
how is it ?

1264
01:29:21,292 --> 01:29:23,252
It's perfect.

1265
01:29:26,088 --> 01:29:30,301
- I got the red foulard okay, didn't I ?
- Yeah, real dark red.

1266
01:29:30,384 --> 01:29:32,762
Burgundy, Charlie,
burgundy.

1267
01:29:32,845 --> 01:29:35,723
They love it.

1268
01:29:35,765 --> 01:29:38,392
Bay Rum.

1269
01:29:39,393 --> 01:29:42,438
Windsor knot.

1270
01:29:42,521 --> 01:29:45,399
[ Sigh ] That's my heart
I'm feelin'.

1271
01:29:54,158 --> 01:29:56,160
I'm off.

1272
01:30:14,345 --> 01:30:16,305
Can you get long distance
on this ?

1273
01:30:16,389 --> 01:30:18,391
And how.
Be my guest.

1274
01:30:29,860 --> 01:30:32,738
- Sugarbush lodge.
- Hi. George Willis, please ?

1275
01:30:32,822 --> 01:30:35,408
One moment, please.

1276
01:30:36,200 --> 01:30:38,160
- Hello ?
- Ah, Harry ?

1277
01:30:38,244 --> 01:30:40,496
Chas, how are you ?

1278
01:30:40,580 --> 01:30:43,749
You just caught us. We're about
to shoot George over to the airport.

1279
01:30:43,833 --> 01:30:46,669
Why is George
going to the airport ?

1280
01:30:46,711 --> 01:30:50,089
Um, hold on. Maybe you should talk
to the man himself.

1281
01:30:51,382 --> 01:30:53,426
- Chas.
- Yeah. Hi, George.

1282
01:30:53,509 --> 01:30:57,471
- You just caught me.
- Harry said. Where you goin' ?

1283
01:30:57,555 --> 01:31:00,057
- Home.
- To Boston ?

1284
01:31:00,141 --> 01:31:03,019
Catching the puddle jumper.
Keep your fingers crossed.

1285
01:31:03,102 --> 01:31:06,606
What are you
going home for ?

1286
01:31:06,689 --> 01:31:10,443
[ Sigh ] I was thinking, Chas.
This asshole, Trask ?

1287
01:31:10,526 --> 01:31:13,195
He's making
no sense at all.

1288
01:31:13,279 --> 01:31:17,033
Somebody's gotta talk to him.
My father's Class of '59.

1289
01:31:17,074 --> 01:31:20,912
Your father ? I thought we were
gonna keep our parents outta this.

1290
01:31:20,995 --> 01:31:25,249
This guy Trask is outta control, Chas.
Outta control !

1291
01:31:25,333 --> 01:31:27,627
Somebody's gotta
talk to him.

1292
01:31:27,710 --> 01:31:31,672
- My father's a major
fund-raiser, you know.
- No, I didn't.

1293
01:31:31,756 --> 01:31:35,509
Just relax.
He'll get us off the hook.

1294
01:31:35,593 --> 01:31:38,721
- I gotta go. Everything all right ?
- Sure.

1295
01:31:38,804 --> 01:31:42,683
- I'll see you Monday. Good-bye.
- Bye.

1296
01:32:06,958 --> 01:32:09,418
- Good night, sir.
- Good night.

1297
01:32:21,305 --> 01:32:23,266
Hiya, Charlie.

1298
01:32:24,809 --> 01:32:26,811
Watch the door.

1299
01:32:44,704 --> 01:32:47,248
What a beautiful woman.

1300
01:33:00,469 --> 01:33:04,432
- Hello, there.
- Do you see what I see ?

1301
01:33:04,515 --> 01:33:07,643
[ TV ] Yeah.
Either there's something wrong,

1302
01:33:07,727 --> 01:33:10,146
or we got the
world's worst hangover.

1303
01:33:10,229 --> 01:33:14,400
Won't you come in ?

1304
01:33:14,483 --> 01:33:16,444
[ TV Off ]

1305
01:33:32,418 --> 01:33:34,378
Colonel ?

1306
01:33:46,974 --> 01:33:50,269
Colonel,
you all right ?

1307
01:33:50,353 --> 01:33:53,189
What is there ?

1308
01:33:56,776 --> 01:34:01,989
It's afternoon.
You've been sleeping all morning.

1309
01:34:02,073 --> 01:34:04,700
So what ?

1310
01:34:04,784 --> 01:34:08,412
I don't know.
I thought --

1311
01:34:12,792 --> 01:34:14,835
I-l talked to George
last night.

1312
01:34:14,919 --> 01:34:17,129
His, ah --

1313
01:34:17,213 --> 01:34:21,592
His father's a big-deal alumnus
at school. He's got a lot of pull.

1314
01:34:21,676 --> 01:34:24,720
Really ?

1315
01:34:24,804 --> 01:34:28,558
Yeah, he's, ah,

1316
01:34:28,641 --> 01:34:30,935
he's gonna talk
to the headmaster.

1317
01:34:31,018 --> 01:34:34,313
George thinks he might
be able to get us off the hook.

1318
01:34:34,397 --> 01:34:37,066
"Get us off the hook."

1319
01:34:37,149 --> 01:34:39,902
Yeah, that's --
that's what he said.

1320
01:34:39,944 --> 01:34:43,781
Watch the "us" part.

1321
01:34:45,616 --> 01:34:48,452
Colonel, don't you wanna
get up and do something ?

1322
01:34:48,536 --> 01:34:51,497
[ Groan ]

1323
01:34:52,665 --> 01:34:54,500
Colonel ?

1324
01:34:54,584 --> 01:34:58,170
Oh, Charlie,
what do ya want ?

1325
01:34:58,254 --> 01:35:00,214
I don't know !

1326
01:35:00,298 --> 01:35:03,426
But you're
making me nervous.

1327
01:35:06,387 --> 01:35:09,557
My wallet is on
the dresser.

1328
01:35:09,640 --> 01:35:11,851
Take out
your plane ticket...

1329
01:35:11,934 --> 01:35:16,772
and $400
mustering-out pay,

1330
01:35:16,814 --> 01:35:19,233
plus...

1331
01:35:19,317 --> 01:35:23,696
airport-to-school taxi.

1332
01:35:25,156 --> 01:35:28,242
Colonel, it's no rush.
I mean, I can --

1333
01:35:28,326 --> 01:35:30,328
I could stay
for a while.

1334
01:35:30,411 --> 01:35:34,290
Charlie, you already
gave me a day.

1335
01:35:34,332 --> 01:35:38,294
For that day,
I am eternally grateful.

1336
01:35:40,087 --> 01:35:44,800
But right now I have...
other plans.

1337
01:35:44,884 --> 01:35:47,511
What other plans
do you have ?

1338
01:35:49,639 --> 01:35:51,641
To die, son.

1339
01:35:51,724 --> 01:35:55,853
Colonel, you're --

1340
01:35:55,937 --> 01:35:58,648
Come on, Colonel,
you're not gonna die today.

1341
01:35:58,689 --> 01:36:02,485
Charlie,
give me your hand.

1342
01:36:06,364 --> 01:36:08,991
You go now, boy.
Okay ?

1343
01:36:10,826 --> 01:36:13,871
You go.
Just, uh --

1344
01:36:16,457 --> 01:36:18,793
Just leave me
sleep here.

1345
01:36:19,877 --> 01:36:23,047
Look, uh --
Can we start over, please ?

1346
01:36:23,130 --> 01:36:27,343
What do you feel
like doin' today, huh ?

1347
01:36:27,426 --> 01:36:29,929
I mean, look at this.
The sun is shining !

1348
01:36:30,012 --> 01:36:32,473
It's a beautiful day.
Let's --

1349
01:36:35,810 --> 01:36:39,313
Colonel, I know you don't want
to be a party poop,

1350
01:36:39,397 --> 01:36:43,401
so let's go out and do something, huh ?
Let's go for a ride.

1351
01:36:48,656 --> 01:36:50,783
Yeah, a ride.

1352
01:36:50,866 --> 01:36:54,078
A ride ?

1353
01:36:54,161 --> 01:36:57,873
Yeah, Colonel Slade,
what do you say ?

1354
01:36:57,957 --> 01:37:01,002
Let's go for a ride,
huh ?

1355
01:37:07,758 --> 01:37:10,094
What kind of ride ?

1356
01:37:11,512 --> 01:37:13,723
Yeah, this is a valid
Oregon driver's license,

1357
01:37:14,265 --> 01:37:17,727
and we let appropriate customers
test-drive the Testarossa.

1358
01:37:17,810 --> 01:37:21,814
But you're 17 and with
a blind companion. That we don't do.

1359
01:37:21,898 --> 01:37:24,817
This is a $190,000
piece of machinery.

1360
01:37:24,901 --> 01:37:28,279
- I'm not letting it out this door.
- How 'bout this one over here ?

1361
01:37:28,362 --> 01:37:31,198
That's a Cabriolet T.
The same deal.

1362
01:37:31,282 --> 01:37:35,578
Think I'm gonna let an unaccompanied kid
get behind the wheel of a $110,000 car ?

1363
01:37:35,661 --> 01:37:38,164
He will not be
unaccompanied.

1364
01:37:38,247 --> 01:37:41,834
I'll be with him.
I'm his father.

1365
01:37:41,918 --> 01:37:44,879
- You're his father ?
- Yes.

1366
01:37:44,962 --> 01:37:48,257
I have an idea. Why don't I take
your father for a test-drive ?

1367
01:37:48,341 --> 01:37:52,261
- What's your quota, Freddie ?
- Don't worry about my quota. I do well.

1368
01:37:52,303 --> 01:37:54,347
How many Ferraris
you sold this month ?

1369
01:37:54,430 --> 01:37:57,099
That's not relevant
to this discussion.

1370
01:37:57,183 --> 01:37:59,268
Freddie,
the 80s are over.

1371
01:37:59,352 --> 01:38:02,063
Are you tryin' to tell me
these are just walkin' outta the store ?

1372
01:38:02,146 --> 01:38:06,317
This is a Ferrari, the finest machinery
made in the automobile industry.

1373
01:38:06,400 --> 01:38:09,278
If you like it that much,
why are you sellin' it ?

1374
01:38:09,362 --> 01:38:14,200
- I'd love to accommodate you --
- If this car performs
the way I expect it to,

1375
01:38:14,283 --> 01:38:19,747
you'll get a certified check of $101,000
and change when in you come tomorrow.

1376
01:38:19,830 --> 01:38:24,377
It's $109,000,
plus $950, plus tax.

1377
01:38:24,460 --> 01:38:27,421
Freddie, for you...

1378
01:38:27,505 --> 01:38:29,674
107 all in,

1379
01:38:29,757 --> 01:38:33,302
plus a case of champagne
to go with your leftover turkey.

1380
01:38:33,386 --> 01:38:37,306
What do you say ?
Don't worry about the boy.

1381
01:38:37,348 --> 01:38:40,977
He drives so smooth,
you can boil an egg on the engine.

1382
01:38:41,060 --> 01:38:44,146
When we bring the car back,
I'll peel the egg for ya.

1383
01:38:44,230 --> 01:38:48,192
Listen, you made me laugh,
but I can't let the car go out.

1384
01:38:50,278 --> 01:38:52,238
Want a deposit ?

1385
01:38:52,321 --> 01:38:55,283
This is not an
installment item, sir.

1386
01:38:58,452 --> 01:39:02,456
Freddie, you're no
spring chicken, are ya ?

1387
01:39:04,166 --> 01:39:08,421
Well, you know what they call me
at the home office ? The gray ghost.

1388
01:39:08,504 --> 01:39:10,840
You know why they
still keep me around ?

1389
01:39:10,881 --> 01:39:14,260
There's no kid here that
can move a Ferrari like I can.

1390
01:39:14,343 --> 01:39:17,221
I'm known from coast to coast
like butter and toast.

1391
01:39:17,305 --> 01:39:19,557
Ask anybody about
Freddie Bisco.

1392
01:39:19,640 --> 01:39:22,560
When I get a Ferrari...
out the door !

1393
01:39:22,643 --> 01:39:26,272
- Hah ! You just made me laugh.
- Yeah ?

1394
01:39:26,355 --> 01:39:30,234
Two thousand.

1395
01:39:30,318 --> 01:39:33,195
Unless you take it,
you're gonna make me cry.

1396
01:39:36,490 --> 01:39:39,535
I'm a gray ghost too.

1397
01:39:49,712 --> 01:39:52,798
See ? This is fun,
isn't it ?

1398
01:40:02,850 --> 01:40:05,811
[ Engine Sputtering ]

1399
01:40:05,895 --> 01:40:09,273
- [ Engine Stops ]
- Drop her into neutral.

1400
01:40:09,357 --> 01:40:12,318
Slide her into second.
Pop the clutch.

1401
01:40:16,280 --> 01:40:19,325
[ Engine Revving ]

1402
01:40:50,439 --> 01:40:54,193
Straight. Hold it
right like that. Feel it ?

1403
01:40:54,235 --> 01:40:57,822
That's straight.
Just keep it straight.

1404
01:41:00,408 --> 01:41:03,411
- Keep it straight.
- No fun just to keep it straight.

1405
01:41:03,494 --> 01:41:06,789
You've got to move a little bit,
feel the road.

1406
01:41:06,872 --> 01:41:09,875
Please ? Just like this.
All right ? There you go.

1407
01:41:09,917 --> 01:41:12,878
[ Charlie ]
Take it nice and easy.

1408
01:41:12,920 --> 01:41:15,965
Do you like this ?

1409
01:41:18,092 --> 01:41:21,429
Slow it down a little.
You goin' a little fast.

1410
01:41:21,512 --> 01:41:24,932
Colonel, slow it down.

1411
01:41:25,016 --> 01:41:27,393
Something's happened
to my foot !

1412
01:41:28,978 --> 01:41:30,938
- Slow it down, please.
- Hold on, Charlie.

1413
01:41:31,022 --> 01:41:33,190
I think I've got
another gear.

1414
01:41:33,274 --> 01:41:35,026
Colonel Slade ?

1415
01:41:37,111 --> 01:41:39,488
- Whoo-ah !
- Oh shit !

1416
01:41:39,572 --> 01:41:42,283
Watch out !

1417
01:41:42,366 --> 01:41:44,327
Hah-hah !

1418
01:41:44,410 --> 01:41:46,621
You'll get us killed !

1419
01:41:46,704 --> 01:41:50,666
Don't blame me, Charlie.
I can't see !

1420
01:41:50,750 --> 01:41:53,711
- Colonel, slow it down !
- [ Laughing ]

1421
01:42:01,802 --> 01:42:04,639
Oh, God.
Oh, Jesus !

1422
01:42:04,680 --> 01:42:07,475
Now let's see
how this baby corners.

1423
01:42:07,558 --> 01:42:10,519
- Corners ?
- Yeah. Say when.

1424
01:42:10,603 --> 01:42:13,231
- Say when what ?
- Say when to turn.

1425
01:42:13,314 --> 01:42:16,776
- Colonel, you can't turn the car.
- Where's the turn, Charlie ?

1426
01:42:16,859 --> 01:42:20,905
3:00 ? 2:00 ?
Right oblique ? Right face ?

1427
01:42:20,988 --> 01:42:22,698
Come on !
Talk to me !

1428
01:42:22,782 --> 01:42:25,159
Ah... it's left, I guess.

1429
01:42:25,243 --> 01:42:27,954
Left. I knew it.
Okay. Now ?

1430
01:42:30,081 --> 01:42:32,667
No, no !
Not now ! Not now !

1431
01:42:32,750 --> 01:42:35,586
- Now ?
